busConfNextId.name: busConfNextId
busConfNextId.description: The next available BUS index. The value of this object can be used as the index by the network manager to create an entry in the busConfTable.

busConfTable.name: busConfTable
busConfTable.description: This table contains all LAN Emulation Broadcast and Unknown Servers (BUS) this agent manages. The BUS handles data sent by an LE Client to the broadcast MAC address, all multicast traffic, and initial unicast frames which are sent by a LEC before the data direct target ATM address has been resolved. There can be multiple BUSs per ELAN, but a BUS can service only one ELAN.

busConfEntry.name: busConfEntry
busConfEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents a BUS. The parameters in each entry apply to one emulated LAN served by one BUS. Object busRowStatus is required during row creation and deletion. Object busElanName is used to indicate the ELAN this BUS is servicing and is used to cross reference tables defined in the LAN Emulation Server MIB. Note that objects busAtmAddrSpec and busAtmAddrMask are used to configure the ATM address of a BUS. The BUS typically derives it's ATM address from the switch or the network and the actual ATM address used is indicated in the object busAtmAddrActual.

busConfIndex.name: busConfIndex
busConfIndex.description: A value which uniquely identifies a conceptual row in the busConfTable. If the conceptual row identified by this value of busConfIndex is recreated following an agent restart, the same value of busConfIndex must be used to identify the recreated row.

busConfAtmAddrSpec.name: busConfAtmAddrSpec
busConfAtmAddrSpec.description: An ATM address specified by the network or local management that, with the ATM address mask, determines a portion of the ATM address that the BUS on the designated ATM interface will use to derive the actual ATM address from the network or ILMI. The derived ATM address is specified in the object busAtmAddrActual, which is used to receive multicast or broadcast traffic.

busConfAtmAddrMask.name: busConfAtmAddrMask
busConfAtmAddrMask.description: The ATM address mask associated with the object busAtmAddrSpec. The value of the mask is an ATM address with the don't care portion set to zero and the valid ATM address portion set to one.

busConfAtmAddrActual.name: busConfAtmAddrActual
busConfAtmAddrActual.description: The resultant ATM address in use by the BUS. This object is a product of the specified ATM address, mask and interaction with the network. This object is created by the agent.

busConfElanName.name: busConfElanName
busConfElanName.description: The name of the ELAN this BUS is providing service to.

busConfLastChange.name: busConfLastChange
busConfLastChange.description: The value of the sysUpTime when this BUS has entered the state indicated by the object busConfOperStatus.

busConfMaxFrameAge.name: busConfMaxFrameAge
busConfMaxFrameAge.reference: LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification - version 1.0. S5.
busConfMaxFrameAge.description: Time out period for a frame that has been received but not been transmitted by BUS to all relevant Multicast Send VCCs or Multicast Forward VCCs.

busConfOperStatus.name: busConfOperStatus
busConfOperStatus.description: The operational state of this BUS entry. When in 'up' state the BUS will forward LEC traffic. Any other state the BUS is not available for service and may release all the existing VCCs and refuse service to all clients.

busConfAdminStatus.name: busConfAdminStatus
busConfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the designated BUS as prescribed by the operator. The actions of the agent will, if at all possible, eventually result in the desired state being reflected in the busOperStatus.

busConfRowStatus.name: busConfRowStatus
busConfRowStatus.reference: RFC 1443, [10] Textual Conventions for version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMPv2).
busConfRowStatus.description: This object is used to create or delete entries in the busConfTable.

busVccTable.name: busVccTable
busVccTable.description: This table contains all the Multicast Forward VCCs used by the BUS to forward multicast traffic to the participating LECs. The Multicast Forward VCC can either be point-to-point or point-to- multipoint calls. This table is read only if SVCs are used and writable if PVCs are used.

busVccEntry.name: busVccEntry
busVccEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents a Multicast Forward VCC of the BUS.

busVccAtmIfIndex.name: busVccAtmIfIndex
busVccAtmIfIndex.description: The ATM interface which the Multicast Forward VCC is running on. This value must match an existing value in the ifTable. The value of this object is set to zero when the ATM interface is undefined.

busVccMtFwdVpi.name: busVccMtFwdVpi
busVccMtFwdVpi.description: The VPI value of the Multicast Forward VCC. The object busVccAtmIfIndex, busVccMtFwdVci and the value of this object uniquely identfies a VCC within a ATM host.

busVccMtFwdVci.name: busVccMtFwdVci
busVccMtFwdVci.description: The VCI value of the Multicast Forward VCC. The object busVccAtmIfIndex, busVccMtFwdVpi and the value of this object uniquely identfies a VCC within a ATM host.

busVccRowStatus.name: busVccRowStatus
busVccRowStatus.reference: RFC 1443, [10] Textual Conventions for version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMPv2).
busVccRowStatus.description: This object is used to create or delete entries in the busConfTable.

busLecTableLastChange.name: busLecTableLastChange
busLecTableLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime when an entry of the busLecTable was created/deleted.

busLecTable.name: busLecTable
busLecTable.description: This table contains the BUS and the actual LECs being serviced by the BUS. It can be used as the actual mapping between BUS and LEC. This table provides information for Multicast send VCCs between BUS and clients. Objects busLecMcastSendAtmIfIndex, busLecMcastSendVpi, and busLecMcstSendVci can only be modified if PVC is used.

busLecEntry.name: busLecEntry
busLecEntry.description: Each entry represents a BUS to LEC mapping.

busLecAtmAddr.name: busLecAtmAddr
busLecAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the LEC. This is the primary ATM address of the LEC.

busLecMcastSendAtmIfIndex.name: busLecMcastSendAtmIfIndex
busLecMcastSendAtmIfIndex.description: The ATM interface index this BUS uses for Multicast Send traffic. The value of this object has to exist in the ifTable in MIB II unless an internal connection is used. When an internal connection is used, this object is set to zero.

busLecMcastSendVpi.name: busLecMcastSendVpi
busLecMcastSendVpi.description: The virtual path identifier used to receive multicast traffic by this BUS.

busLecMcastSendVci.name: busLecMcastSendVci
busLecMcastSendVci.description: The virtual channel identifier used to receive multicast traffic by this BUS.

busLecRowStatus.name: busLecRowStatus
busLecRowStatus.description: This object provides a way for the network manager to selectively remove a LE Client from the designated BUS. Or in a system where PVCs are used, this table is used to create Multicast Send VCCs between BUS and LEC.

busStatTable.name: busStatTable
busStatTable.description: This table contains all counters the BUS maintain. This table is an extention to the busConfTable.

busStatEntry.name: busStatEntry
busStatEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains a BUS and its counters.

busStatInDiscards.name: busStatInDiscards
busStatInDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded due to resource error.

busStatInOctets.name: busStatInOctets
busStatInOctets.description: The number of octets that this BUS has received since its initialization.

busStatInUcastFrms.name: busStatInUcastFrms
busStatInUcastFrms.description: The number of frames that the BUS has received which were unicast data frames and all control frames (i.e. they were flooded from the client).

busStatInMcastFrms.name: busStatInMcastFrms
busStatInMcastFrms.description: The number of frames that the BUS has received which were multicast frames.

busStatFrmTimeOuts.name: busStatFrmTimeOuts
busStatFrmTimeOuts.description: The number of frames dropped by the BUS due to time out.

busStatMcastSendRefused.name: busStatMcastSendRefused
busStatMcastSendRefused.description: The number of multicast send VCCconnection setup attempts to the BUS which were refused.

busStatMcastFwdFailure.name: busStatMcastFwdFailure
busStatMcastFwdFailure.description: The number of multicast forward VCCconnection setup attempts from the BUS which were unsuccessful for any reason.

busLecStatTable.name: busLecStatTable
busLecStatTable.description: This table contains all LEC counters the BUS maintains. This table can also be used to retrieve all LECs a BUS is providing service to.

busLecStatEntry.name: busLecStatEntry
busLecStatEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents a LEC and its counters.

busLecRecvs.name: busLecRecvs
busLecRecvs.description: Number of Multicast, Broadcast and Unknown Forward requests received by the BUS from this LEC.

busLecForwards.name: busLecForwards
busLecForwards.description: Number of Multicast, Broadcast and Unkown Forward requests forwarded by the BUS from this LEC. The value of this object indicate how many requests have been forwarded by the BUS.

busLecDiscards.name: busLecDiscards
busLecDiscards.description: Number of Multicast, Broadcast and Unkown Forward requests discarded by the BUS from this LEC. The value of this object indicate how many requests have been discarded by the BUS.

busErrCtlTable.name: busErrCtlTable
busErrCtlTable.description: This table contains error log control information of all BUS instances. This table is an extention to the busConfTable. It is used to enable or disable error logs for a particular BUS entry.

busErrCtlEntry.name: busErrCtlEntry
busErrCtlEntry.description: Each entry represents a BUS entry in the busConfTable.

busErrCtlAdminStatus.name: busErrCtlAdminStatus
busErrCtlAdminStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable error logging for the BUS.

busErrCtlOperStatus.name: busErrCtlOperStatus
busErrCtlOperStatus.description: This object is used to indicate the result of a set operation to the object busErrCtlAdminStatus. If the error log was successfully started, it is in active(2) mode. Otherwise, it is set to either outOfRes(3) or failed(4) for the respective reasons.

busErrCtlClearLog.name: busErrCtlClearLog
busErrCtlClearLog.description: This object is used to clear the error log entries associated with this BUS.

busErrCtlMaxEntries.name: busErrCtlMaxEntries
busErrCtlMaxEntries.description: The maximum entries of the error log a BUS can support.

busErrCtlLastEntry.name: busErrCtlLastEntry
busErrCtlLastEntry.description: The index to the last entry in the error log table for this BUS.

busErrLogTable.name: busErrLogTable
busErrLogTable.description: This table contains error logs of the BUS instances enabled in the busErrCtlTable. This table is indexed by the BUS instance index and an arbitrary integer uniquely identifies an error log.

busErrLogEntry.name: busErrLogEntry
busErrLogEntry.description: Each entry represents aan error detected by the BUS.

busErrLogIndex.name: busErrLogIndex
busErrLogIndex.description: An arbitrary integer which uniquely identifies an error log entry. The first entry after reset or clearing the error log is an assigned value (2^32-1). Succeding entries are assigned with descending values consecutively. Entries after 1 are discarded.The enabling/disabling of the error log capability is done in the busErrCtlTable.

busErrLogAtmAddr.name: busErrLogAtmAddr
busErrLogAtmAddr.description: The primary ATM address of the LE Client on whose Multicast Send VCC the error occured. The corresponding error code is specified in the object busErrLogErrCode.

busErrLogErrCode.name: busErrLogErrCode
busErrLogErrCode.description: The Error code which indicates the cause of the error.

busErrLogTime.name: busErrLogTime
busErrLogTime.description: The sysUpTime when this entry was logged by the BUS.
